         "id": "SECTION_introduction",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "### Introduction\n\nSo far, we have seen that, in the Indo-Arabic numerals we use, the numerical order (or families, as we mentioned in the *History Tracers*) ) grows as we write numbers to the left (<htcite0>; <htcite1>).\n\nWhen observing the indigenous numbers of the Americas (*Abya Yala*), we notice that the numerical orders increase vertically (<htcite2>; <htcite3>). It is worth remembering that, in the Americas (*Abya Yala*), the Yupana represents numbers horizontally, although the orders are represented vertically (<htcite4>).\n\nWe have already seen different ways of representing quantities, although all of them represent exactly the same idea of numerical families (orders).",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "00f3ab60-2017-420a-99dc-56de384243e8",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team",
